,"results_url":"https://hbcnewsroom.co.uk/halton-council-local-elections-2026/","candidates":[{"n":"Gareth Charles Stockton","p":"Liberal Democrats","v":1201,"r":1,"e":true,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"16065","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/16065/eedd6e72-22f7-4fd8-b40d-4cfcda0aca31.png"},{"n":"David Roberts","p":"Reform UK","v":1063,"r":2,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"127065","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/127065/87d2a203-4898-41c2-8824-62d9d5f6e389.png"},{"n":"Julian David Gardiner","p":"Green Party","v":356,"r":3,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"127064"},{"n":"Dan Clarke","p":"Libertarian Party","v":69,"r":4,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"existing","cf":"high","pid":"19433","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/19433/541469dd-be01-40d7-9b94-53a6880b3494.png","stmt":"The LPUK is proud to announce our candidate for Beechwood & Heath: Dan Clarke\n\nDan is the Northern Co-ordinator for the Libertarian Party and is a seasoned campaigner, having twice stood in Parliamentary elections and at local council level on multiple occasions.","bd":"1988"}]},{"ward":"Birchfield","seats":1,"turnout_pct":null,"results_url":"https://hbcnewsroom.co.uk/halton-council-local-elections-2026/","candidates":[{"n":"James Michael Coopersmith","p":"Reform UK","v":837,"r":1,"e":true,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"127470","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/127470/fb84bd2d-02e5-4e76-bb8d-817018c5b177.png"},{"n":"Mike Fry","p":"Labour Party","v":835,"r":2,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"existing","cf":"high","pid":"39243","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/39243/ff42bf6a-95c3-4685-bfcb-af2b00f43848.png","stmt":"I am married with 4 children, all born and educated in Widnes. I have lived in the borough at the same address for 42 years.\r\n\r\nI run my own local business, which was established in 1985 and has always had its base in Widnes.\r\n\r\nI am heavily involved in the local charity scene and I am a board member at Halton & St Helens Voluntary Community Action having been the Chair for a number of years previously."},{"n":"Joseph Christopher Scholes","p":"Green Party","v":340,"r":3,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"127471"},{"n":"John Robert Powell","p":"Conservative and Unionist Party","v":339,"r":4,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"existing","cf":"high","pid":"14248","stmt":"Dear fellow Birchfield Residents,\n\nI am again standing in the Local Councillor Elections on Thursday, 6th May 2021.\n\nThis year all current councillors are subject to re-election following the changes made to some Ward boundaries. This affects Birchfield as we have lost the Heathfield and Poleacre estates to Hough Green Ward, whilst gaining part of the North East section of Farnworth Ward, principally Cronton Road and Norlands Lane, together with the estates leading off there.\n\nOur current councillors, do not reside in Birchfield and whilst this should not disqualify them from standing, I believe that if you don't live in an area you don't have a daily feel for its pulse and issues. I know that non-residency of candidates is a regular feature in Parliamentary elections, but these are community elections so different in my view.\n\nI have lived in Birchfield for more than 35 years and indeed went to school all those years ago at Wade Deacon.\n\nFollowing issues in early 2019, I decided to commit some of my spare time to making a difference where I live. This started with simple litter picking on a daily basis, which then escalated to strimming and cutting back brambles and weed on verges and fence lines. To facilitate and formalise these activities I set up Birchfield Ward Community Association (BWCA) in late 2019. The activity is undertaken in collaboration with various departments of HBC.\n\nSo I'm invested in Birchfield and want to do more. My being elected as a Birchfield councillor will not change anything at the council. Halton is a Labour stronghold. So I'm not going to say I can bring change in the borough, but I will ask the important questions and raise my concerns, as I have done regarding erosion of the Green Belt in Birchfield.\n\nWhat I will do is champion your concerns about the borough but more importantly about Birchfield. There is much to be done in Birchfield. More houses will bring further strain on our road system and infrastructure. We have no community "}]},{"ward":"Bridgewater","seats":1,"turnout_pct":null,"results_url":"https://hbcnewsroom.co.uk/halton-council-local-elections-2026/","candidates":[{"n":"Sarah Davies","p":"Reform UK","v":876,"r":1,"e":true,"g":"female","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"128088","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/128088/773e15c5-11ab-438f-bd88-60d123c1a977.png"},{"n":"Mark David Dennett","p":"Labour Party","v":561,"r":2,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"39262","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/39262/f03eb113-d9f2-4404-abb0-941660ec2d71.png"},{"n":"Deborah Brooks","p":"Green Party","v":348,"r":3,"e":false,"g":"female","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"109643"},{"n":"Suzanne Nicola Howard","p":"Liberal Democrats","v":90,"r":4,"e":false,"g":"female","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"79629"},{"n":"Matthew John Quinn","p":"Conservative and Unionist Party","v":64,"r":5,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"128089"}]},{"ward":"Central & West Bank","seats":1,"turnout_pct":null,"results_url":"https://hbcnewsroom.co.uk/halton-council-local-elections-2026/","candidates":[{"n":"Jonathan David MacKie","p":"Reform UK","v":662,"r":1,"e":true,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"127513","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/127513/ae7d80ba-2161-4422-a294-22560bbafdce.png"},{"n":"Ian Wall","p":"Labour Party","v":369,"r":2,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"127514"},{"n":"Aubrey Kelly","p":"Green Party","v":208,"r":3,"e":false,"g":"female","m":"claude","cf":"high","pid":"127512","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/127512/905077b8-e7b3-4ae5-a5ec-645cd5837934.png","stmt":"Aubrey was born in Widnes and has lived in the town centre for the majority of their life. She is incredibly passionate about the local community and will do all she can to serve Widnes' residents. Whether that is by improving youth programmes to target antisocial behaviour, supporting and protecting local green spaces, or listening to the needs and desires of local businesses. Aubrey understands that many residents feel that they aren't being heard or seen by their Council, and they aim to change that."},{"n":"Julie Powell","p":"Conservative and Unionist Party","v":45,"r":4,"e":false,"g":"female","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"39288"}]},{"ward":"Daresbury, Moore & Sandymoor","seats":2,"turnout_pct":null,"results_url":"https://hbcnewsroom.co.uk/halton-council-local-elections-2026/","candidates":[{"n":"John David Scott","p":"Reform UK","v":728,"r":1,"e":true,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"127891"},{"n":"Dylan Anthony Eaton","p":"Reform UK","v":725,"r":2,"e":true,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"92688","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/92688/7c5fbc6e-c7e9-4f90-9160-d7ad0f0ef743.png"},{"n":"Jo Jones","p":"Labour Party","v":664,"r":3,"e":false,"g":"female","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"127889","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/127889/025f06ce-1d5b-412c-87a1-8163c8b12022.png"},{"n":"Geoffrey Michael Logan","p":"Labour Party","v":609,"r":4,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"16000","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/16000/1bb67fd